{"data":{"names":[{"dateOfBirth":"1970","placeOfBirth":" New York City, New York, USA","height":"5' 7\" (1.7 m)","bio":"Peyman Maadi was born in 1972 in New York City to an Iranian couple. His father was a lawyer. His family moved back to Iran when he was 5 years old. He graduated in Metallurgical Engineering from Karaj Azad University. Maadi started his film career as a screenwriter in late 2000s. He is the writer of several famous Iranian films. He started his acting career in Asghar Farhadi's film À propos d'Elly (2009). Two years later, he received the Silver Bear award for Best Actor in Leading Role for his performance as Nader in Farhadi's A Separation (2011) from the Berlin International Film Festival.","urlPhoto":"https://images-na.ssl-images-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQzMTI2NDQ5NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjM3Mjc1MjE@._V1.jpg","urlIMDB":"http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1818216","name":"Peyman Moaadi","idIMDB":"nm1818216","filmographies":[{"section":"Actor","filmography":[{"title":"Bomb","year":" 2017","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt6210132"},{"title":"The Night Of","year":" 2016","remarks":["(TV Mini-Series)"],"imdbid":"tt2401256"},{"title":"Window Horses","year":" 2016","remarks":["Payman (voice)"],"imdbid":"tt4181270"},{"title":"Life+1Day","year":" 2016","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt5460658"},{"title":"13 Hours","year":" 2016","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt4172430"},{"title":"Last Knights","year":" 2015","remarks":["Emperor (as Payman Maadi)"],"imdbid":"tt2493486"},{"title":"Tales","year":" 2014","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt3526482"},{"title":"Melbourne","year":" 2014","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt3520564"},{"title":"Camp X-Ray","year":" 2014","remarks":["(as Payman Maadi)"],"imdbid":"tt2994190"},{"title":"Querelles","year":" 2011","remarks":["Masoud (voice)"],"imdbid":"tt1855282"},{"title":"A Separation","year":" 2011","remarks":["(as Peyman Moadi)"],"imdbid":"tt1832382"},{"title":"À propos d'Elly","year":" 2009","remarks":null,"imdbid":"tt1360860"}]},{"section":"Writer","filmogr